medical cost of U.S. dollars 605,131 per quality-adjusted life year at 3 months 
to U.S. dollars 94,169 at 24 months after transplantation. The results were 
sensitive to medical cost.
CONCLUSIONS: Follow-up survey identified progressive increases in the 
cost-effectiveness of living donor liver transplantation for patients with 
end-stage liver disease. Living donor liver transplantation appears to represent 
a cost-effective medical technology.

