OBJECTIVE: Aggressive chemotherapy and radiotherapy or radical oncological 
surgery in young women with cancer has greatly enhanced these patients' life 
expectancy, but these treatments often cause infertility or premature ovarian 
failure due to a massive destruction of the ovarian reserve. The objective of 
this review is to discuss the effect of the various cancer treatments on 
fertility and present the various fertility sparing operations and fertility 
preservation strategies.
METHOD: An extensive survey of the most up-to-date literature was performed.
